articles.author: Liz Lee, Andrew Hayley
articles.description: China's involvement in Russia's Arctic LNG-2 liquefied natural gas project should not be the target of any third party intervention or restrictions, its foreign ministry said on Tuesday.
articles.title: China criticizes U.S. sanctions on Russia's Arctic LNG-2 project

articles.author: Leika Kihara
articles.description: Some Bank of Japan policymakers called for deeper debate on a future exit from ultra-loose monetary policy as the economy makes progress toward achieving the bank's price target, a summary of opinions at this month's meeting showed on Wednesday.
articles.title: Some in BOJ called for more debate on future easy policy exit -meeting summary

articles.author: Blake Brittain
articles.description: Apple (AAPL.O) on Tuesday appealed a decision to ban imports of its watches based on a complaint from medical monitoring technology company Masimo (MASI.O), after U.S. President Joe Biden's administration declined to veto a government tribunal.
articles.title: Apple files appeal after Biden administration allows US ban on watch imports

articles.author: Jason Xue, Casey Hall
articles.description: Chinese online gaming giant Tencent Holdings (0700.HK) saw its shares stage a mild rebound on Wednesday, the first day of trade after regulators vowed to make improvements to proposed rules that had sent stock in gaming companies plunging.
articles.title: Tencent, NetEase shares rebound after regulators vow to improve proposed rules

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israel's government agreed to give Intel Corp (INTC.O) a $3.2 billion grant for new $25 billion chip plant it plans to build in southern Israel, both sides said on Tuesday.
articles.title: Intel to get $3.2 billion government grant for new $25 billion Israel chip plant

articles.author: Naveen Thukral
articles.description: High food prices in recent years have prompted farmers worldwide to plant more cereals and oilseeds, but consumers are set to face tighter supplies well into 2024, amid adverse El Nino weather, export restrictions and higher biofuel mandates.
articles.title: Global 2024 staple food supplies to be strained by dry weather, export curbs

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Manchester United shares (MANU.N) rose about 3% on Tuesday after a stake purchase by billionaire Jim Ratcliffe cleared months of uncertainty over a deal that fans and investors hoped would revitalize the British soccer club.
articles.title: Manchester United shares rise as Ratcliffe deal eases ownership uncertainty

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Explosions in the Red Sea off the coast of Yemen were reported on Tuesday after sightings of unmanned aircraft and missiles in two separate incidents, a British maritime authority said.
articles.title: Explosions reported in Red Sea shipping lane off Yemen coast

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ukraine carried out an air attack on Feodosia in Crimea, Ukraine's air force commander said on Tuesday, after the Russian-installed governor of the Crimea said that the assault sparked a fire in the town's port area.
articles.title: Ukraine carries out air assault on Crimea's port of Feodosia

articles.author: Jose Torres
articles.description: Thousands of migrants and asylum seekers moved slowly north across the southern Mexican state of Chiapas on Tuesday in a caravan hoping to reach the U.S. border, one day before top U.S. officials planned to visit Mexico to discuss migration.
articles.title: Migrant caravan advances north as U.S. officials head to Mexico
